<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-5008">
<p>The average child watches 28 hours of TV per week and sees 20,000 commercials a year.<br />
Hours per year the average American youth spends in school: 900 hours<br />
Hours per year the average American youth watches television: 1500<br />
(source: <a href="http://www.csun.edu/science/health/docs/tv&#038;health.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.csun.edu/science/health/docs/tv&#038;health.html</a>)</p>
<p>Do we want average children or exceptional children?</p>
<p>I choose exceptional. We ditched the TV years ago, and have no regrets.</p>
